item.title: At Sea
item.description: Distress sealed in a bottle Grief cast out to sea Rolled, roiled, tumbled Returned to shore. It’s eneergy and strength Releases sea glass A smooth survivor Every piece unique.

item.title: Tideline
item.description: I sent my friend a linocut card Bird Watching by Diana Ashdown. And this poem I wrote On a mudflat somewhere Will be an oystercatcher Blissfully unaware Of an onlooker’s envious stare A bird who life is clearly black and white Then whether the moon full and bright Tides will keep on turning
